 `preventDefault()` was not called (checked via mCancelable flag). The system group dispatch (lines 651-693 in EventDispatcher.cpp) allows system code to perform default actions after content listeners have run.\n\n## Complete Dispatch Sequence\n1. EventDispatcher::Dispatch() called with target and WidgetEvent\n2. Event target chain built via GetEventTargetParent() traversal\n3. EventChainPreVisitor set up with initial event state\n4. PreHandleEvent() called on all chain items\n5. HandleEventTargetChain() executes:\n   - Capture phase: root to target, calling capture=true listeners\n   - Target phase: target element with both capture and bubble listeners\n   - Bubble phase: target to root, calling capture=false listeners\n6. For each phase and target, EventListenerManager::HandleEvent() invokes listeners\n7. After default group dispatch, system group dispatch occurs\n8. PostHandleEvent() executes default actions if not prevented\n9. Event propagation complete, results returned to caller"
}

